[src:bioenergy/2022-in-climate-change] Research found that 80–90% of Americans underestimate the prevalence of support for major climate change mitigation policies and climate concern.
[src:bioenergy/2022-in-climate-change] While 66–80% Americans support these policies, Americans estimate the prevalence to be 37–43%.
[src:bioenergy/2022-in-climate-change] National political divides on the seriousness of climate change consistently correlate with political ideology, with right-wing opinion being more negative.
